INTERIOR POINTS may be given to adjust the length of 
triangle edges around theses points as vertices.
The WISHED LENGTH of triangles around the POINT is
an upper BOUND.
   
Example:
1;  {1 closed line}
2;  {2 interior points}
L1; {the name of the closed line}
PTI1; PTI2; {the interior points}
0.01; 0.5;  {the lengths around each interior points}

The triangle edges from PT1 will have a length<0.01
The triangle edges from PT2 will have a length<0.5
